WEBVTT

00:03.303 --> 00:07.673
Wow! I can't believe how
many ponies showed up.

00:07.675 --> 00:13.178
<i>Pony of ceremonies is,</i>
<i>is a pretty big deal.</i>

00:15.682 --> 00:18.450
I didn't know granny smith was
on the selection committee.

00:18.452 --> 00:22.521
<i>Ponyville days celebrates</i>
<i>the founding of ponyville</i>

00:22.523 --> 00:25.691
I'm glad the committee didn't
automatically pick me

00:25.693 --> 00:27.326
So everypony gets
a chance to see

00:27.328 --> 00:32.064
And the pony of ceremonies
organizes the whole thing

00:32.066 --> 00:33.599
So it would make
sense if they picked me.

00:33.601 --> 00:35.401
Shhhhhh!

00:35.403 --> 00:37.169
Citizens of ponyville,

00:37.171 --> 00:40.339
This year's applicants
were all exceptional,

00:40.341 --> 00:42.741
But there can only be
one ponyville days

00:42.743 --> 00:45.077
Pony of ceremonies.

00:45.079 --> 00:47.079
And that pony is...

00:49.115 --> 00:50.482
<i>(big inhale)</i>

00:56.057 --> 00:59.691
<i>Applejack: Whoo whee!</i>
<i>All right, rarity!</i>

00:59.693 --> 01:02.294
<i>(cheers)</i>

01:02.296 --> 01:03.662
Congratulations, rarity.

01:03.664 --> 01:05.631
Do you know what
you're going to do?

01:06.399 --> 01:08.267
(grunts)

01:10.136 --> 01:13.305
Oh, I might have a few ideas.

01:16.709 --> 01:19.745
<i>♪ my little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:19.747 --> 01:21.313
<i>♪ aaaaahhh!</i>

01:21.315 --> 01:26.585
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be ♪</i>

01:26.587 --> 01:30.722
<i>♪ until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me ♪</i>

01:30.724 --> 01:31.824
<i>♪ big adventure</i>

01:37.298 --> 01:47.573
<i>♪ do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:52.545 --> 01:57.549
♪

01:57.551 --> 02:00.552
I'm so excited for the festival
I can hardly stand up straight.

02:00.554 --> 02:02.154
<i>(thud)</i>

02:02.156 --> 02:04.623
Me, too. I'm glad
rarity was picked.

02:04.625 --> 02:07.359
I know she'll add a touch of
elegance to the whole thing.

02:07.361 --> 02:08.894
Probably more than a touch.

02:16.870 --> 02:18.270
Ahem.

02:18.272 --> 02:23.175
This year's ponyville days
festival designed by rarity,

02:23.177 --> 02:27.646
Will feature various high
class events, such as...

02:27.648 --> 02:30.516
<i>A silent cider</i>
<i>auction and tasting...</i>

02:30.518 --> 02:32.384
Ooooh!

02:32.386 --> 02:35.154
<i>A ponyville gala</i>
<i>in town square...</i>

02:35.156 --> 02:40.425
<i>And, of course, a</i>
<i>ponyville fashion show.</i>

02:40.427 --> 02:46.365
This year's ponyville days
festival pony of ceremonies,

02:46.367 --> 02:49.801
Creates shimmering
couture of her own design.

02:51.538 --> 02:59.411
And the theme is,
small town chic!

02:59.413 --> 03:03.315
Wow, rarity! You really have
put a lot of effort into this.

03:03.317 --> 03:04.783
I'll say.

03:04.785 --> 03:08.253
I think it's going
to be magical.

03:08.255 --> 03:09.655
Do you really think so?

03:09.657 --> 03:11.957
Are you kidding?
I can't wait!

03:11.959 --> 03:16.662
But, of course, I couldn't
possibly do it all on my own.

03:16.664 --> 03:19.198
The festival is in three days!

03:19.200 --> 03:21.233
Pinkie pie and I can hang
lights and decorations

03:21.235 --> 03:25.938
And I can get sweet apple acres
all ready for the cider tasting.

03:25.940 --> 03:27.940
That's just perfect.

03:27.942 --> 03:30.576
And now twilight, if you and
fluttershy wouldn't mind helping

03:30.578 --> 03:31.843
With the fashion show...

03:31.845 --> 03:32.945
Of course.

03:32.947 --> 03:37.549
I can focus on the one thing
I'm worried about most of all.

03:37.551 --> 03:38.951
<i>All: What?</i>

03:38.953 --> 03:41.453
Creating a ponyville
days festival

03:41.455 --> 03:43.855
Fantastic enough to impress...

03:43.857 --> 03:45.357
Trenderhoof!

03:49.829 --> 03:51.897
Uh, who's trenderhoof?

03:51.899 --> 03:55.934
How can you not know
who trenderhoof is?

03:55.936 --> 03:58.470
Trenderhoof is only
<u>the</u> most amazing,

03:58.472 --> 04:01.974
Handsomest travel writer to
have ever traveled or written.

04:01.976 --> 04:04.843
Before las pegasus became an
equestria travel destination,

04:04.845 --> 04:08.447
Before the culinary
revolution in trottingham,

04:08.449 --> 04:10.249
He discovered it.

04:10.251 --> 04:13.352
He knows what's going to be hot
even before it's tepid.

04:13.354 --> 04:15.587
<i>(giggle)</i>

04:15.589 --> 04:18.690
Sounds like somepony has
a little bit of a crush.

04:18.692 --> 04:20.459
Oh, twilight.

04:20.461 --> 04:22.794
"crush" doesn't even
begin to describe it!

04:22.796 --> 04:24.529
He's practically divine.

04:24.531 --> 04:25.831
I can't believe he's coming!

04:25.833 --> 04:27.566
<i>(hysterical giggling)</i>

04:31.938 --> 04:36.008
<i>(chugging)</i>

04:36.010 --> 04:37.943
<i>(hiss)</i>

04:40.546 --> 04:42.748
Thank you ever so much
for joining me, twilight.

04:42.750 --> 04:45.684
I don't think I could have
met trenderhoof on my own.

04:45.686 --> 04:47.719
It's no problem, but you
shouldn't be nervous

04:47.721 --> 04:49.488
About meeting him.

04:49.490 --> 04:51.823
<i>(clamouring)</i>

04:51.825 --> 04:54.359
Is that him? Do you see him?
Twilight, is he there?

04:54.361 --> 04:56.561
Uh...I'm not sure.

04:56.563 --> 04:58.430
You don't suppose he
decided not to come?

04:58.432 --> 04:59.731
Twilight, I don't see him!

04:59.733 --> 05:01.033
What if he doesn't arrive?

05:01.035 --> 05:02.834
The whole festival
will be a disaster!

05:02.836 --> 05:04.670
Twilight, where is he?

05:06.606 --> 05:08.473
Ahem. Sorry.

05:08.475 --> 05:10.542
Rarity, you have to
get a hold of yourself.

05:10.544 --> 05:12.477
I mean, you haven't
even met him yet...

05:22.789 --> 05:29.428
<i>♪ (romantic theme)</i>

05:29.430 --> 05:31.096
<i>(huge gasp)</i>

05:31.098 --> 05:32.097
What's wrong?

05:32.099 --> 05:37.102
It's him, it's him, it's
him, he's here, it's him.

05:37.104 --> 05:39.504
Well, go up and talk to him.

05:39.506 --> 05:41.907
<i>(squeaking)</i>

05:41.909 --> 05:43.075
I can't.

05:46.012 --> 05:47.546
<i>(nervous giggle)</i>

05:47.548 --> 05:49.381
Um... Hi. Ahem.

05:49.383 --> 05:54.619
I am rarity and I have been
chosen as pony of ceremonies

05:54.621 --> 05:56.555
For the ponyville days festival.

05:56.557 --> 05:58.957
<i>(giggle)</i>

05:58.959 --> 05:59.958
Please.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.593
Call me trend.

06:04.097 --> 06:05.497
<i>(thud)</i>

06:07.734 --> 06:10.669
And over here will be the
climax of the festival,

06:10.671 --> 06:12.671
The ponyville days gala.

06:12.673 --> 06:14.806
Music. Dancing.

06:14.808 --> 06:18.110
And of course a locally sourced
menu of delicious treats.

06:18.112 --> 06:20.846
Reminds me of the spring fling
meets manehattan wedding

06:20.848 --> 06:22.814
I wrote about in
gallop & prance.

06:22.816 --> 06:25.617
Exactly! I can't
even describe

06:25.619 --> 06:28.019
How much your work
has influenced me.

06:31.691 --> 06:34.860
And finally, sweet apple acres.

06:34.862 --> 06:37.729
Ponyville's core, heh
heh, so to speak,

06:37.731 --> 06:40.399
<i>Where our quaint</i>
<i>little hamlet began.</i>

06:40.401 --> 06:43.435
<i>Trend: Oh! Breathtaking!</i>

06:43.437 --> 06:47.539
I've heard about it, of course,
but to see it in verite,

06:47.541 --> 06:50.942
To stand on the soil
of a working farm.

06:50.944 --> 06:53.111
You can really feel
the authenticity.

06:53.113 --> 06:56.948
Oh yes! Uh, they really
do grow apples here.

06:56.950 --> 06:58.717
Thank you, rarity.

06:58.719 --> 07:00.552
Thank you for
bringing me here.

07:00.554 --> 07:04.156
This farm is truly
something special.

07:04.158 --> 07:07.125
I had planned to transform it
into an elegant country inn

07:07.127 --> 07:13.098
But now I see just how
special it is  <i>au natural.</i>

07:13.100 --> 07:15.066
Au natural, indeed.

07:18.938 --> 07:20.439
<i>(bray)</i>

07:20.441 --> 07:21.873
Who.

07:21.875 --> 07:22.974
Is.

07:22.976 --> 07:24.109
That?

07:28.514 --> 07:32.451
<i>♪ (romantic theme)</i>

07:32.453 --> 07:34.553
Who? Applejack?

07:34.555 --> 07:42.994
<i>♪</i>

07:42.996 --> 07:46.731
Why are you staring
at her like that?

07:46.733 --> 07:49.601
I've seen a lot in
my travels, but...

07:49.603 --> 07:52.838
I've never beheld such beauty.

07:52.840 --> 07:55.207
<i>Applejack.</i>

07:55.209 --> 07:57.776
The pony of my dreams.

08:02.882 --> 08:03.915
<i>Spike: Rarity?</i>

08:03.917 --> 08:05.183
Rarity?

08:05.185 --> 08:06.184
Hello?

08:06.186 --> 08:10.489
<i>(sobbing)</i>

08:10.491 --> 08:12.824
<i>(bawling)</i>

08:12.826 --> 08:14.125
I brought my cider
tasting cup.

08:14.127 --> 08:16.261
Are you ready to
go try the samples?

08:16.263 --> 08:21.533
What's the point?

08:21.535 --> 08:24.102
Rarity, what's wrong?

08:24.104 --> 08:25.804
Nothing.

08:25.806 --> 08:28.039
Is it something I said?

08:28.041 --> 08:29.908
He doesn't like me.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.142
What?

08:31.144 --> 08:32.744
He doesn't like me.

08:32.746 --> 08:37.716
He doesn't like me because
he has a crush on applejack

08:37.718 --> 08:39.885
Even though I've had
a crush on him ever since

08:39.887 --> 08:43.188
The beginning of time
and it's not fair!

08:43.190 --> 08:45.290
Trenderhoof doesn't like you?

08:45.292 --> 08:46.825
That's ridiculous.

08:46.827 --> 08:48.560
<i>(sobbing)</i>

08:48.562 --> 08:50.729
Oh, spike, how could you
ever know what it's like

08:50.731 --> 08:52.731
To be totally
obsessed with a pony

08:52.733 --> 08:54.566
Only to find out
they're obsessed

08:54.568 --> 08:56.635
With somepony else?

08:58.271 --> 09:02.908
I mean, what could applejack
possibly have that I don't?

09:02.910 --> 09:05.143
<i>(I don't know)</i>

09:05.145 --> 09:06.945
Hmmm.

09:09.815 --> 09:12.317
You know, I have such
respect for the work ethic

09:12.319 --> 09:14.219
Of earth ponies.

09:14.221 --> 09:16.688
Uh, gee, thanks.

09:16.690 --> 09:19.157
Granny smith always said,
"pick an apple a day

09:19.159 --> 09:24.062
How many varieties of
apples do you think there are?

09:24.064 --> 09:26.231
On the farm or in all
of equestria because--

09:26.233 --> 09:28.567
I once had
an apple so rare,

09:28.569 --> 09:29.868
They thought it
was extinct.

09:29.870 --> 09:31.069
I ate four of them.

09:31.071 --> 09:32.571
(chomp)

09:34.307 --> 09:36.041
Is that a fact?

09:36.043 --> 09:39.811
I take the mundane,
the simple, the...

09:39.813 --> 09:42.581
Unappreciated, and
I make it relatable.

09:42.583 --> 09:44.716
Well, I hope you can
relate to ponyville.

09:44.718 --> 09:46.017
Me too.

09:46.019 --> 09:47.252
But enough about me.

09:47.254 --> 09:48.820
I want to know about you.

09:48.822 --> 09:51.923
What do apples
mean to applejack?

09:51.925 --> 09:55.060
Look, I'm glad you're
interested in ponyville and all,

09:55.062 --> 09:57.596
But I'm kinda busy
with my chores

09:57.598 --> 09:59.097
And if I can't get 'em done,

09:59.099 --> 10:00.966
There won't be a
ponyville days festival

10:00.968 --> 10:05.170
<i>Rarity: Well, that</i>
<i>will never do!</i>

10:05.172 --> 10:08.707
Rarity, what are you wearing?

10:08.709 --> 10:10.976
What, this old thing?

10:10.978 --> 10:12.877
Aren't you too busy
planning the festival

10:12.879 --> 10:14.779
To keep making new
outfits for it?

10:14.781 --> 10:18.350
I am, but the thought of
hauling apples inspired me

10:18.352 --> 10:20.619
And I just couldn't
stop myself.

10:20.621 --> 10:22.253
Really?

10:22.255 --> 10:26.024
If there's one thing I
love, it's hauling apples.

10:28.361 --> 10:31.196
I'm growing fond
of it, myself.

10:32.999 --> 10:35.867
Maybe you two should
try it sometime.

10:35.869 --> 10:38.870
I'm feeling a tad inspired.

10:38.872 --> 10:42.974
<i>♪ without farm life there'd</i>
<i>be such disparity. ♪</i>

10:42.976 --> 10:46.978
<i>♪ these thoughts I think</i>
<i>with great clarity. ♪</i>

10:46.980 --> 10:52.183
<i>♪ apples high to the sky,</i>
<i>she's the one of my eye. ♪</i>

10:52.185 --> 10:55.787
<i>That fruit hauling</i>
<i>pony named..♪.</i>

10:55.789 --> 10:57.389
<i>♪ ...Applejack.</i>

10:59.291 --> 11:00.792
<i>(smashing glass)</i>

11:03.829 --> 11:06.898
Rarity, why do you
want to plow a field?

11:06.900 --> 11:09.234
Is it me or could this
use a splash of color,

11:09.236 --> 11:10.935
And maybe a wash?

11:10.937 --> 11:13.071
Don't we need to check
on the gala decorations?

11:13.073 --> 11:16.941
But trend obviously has
a thing for farm life.

11:16.943 --> 11:20.011
If I can't convince him that
I'm just as much of a farm hoof

11:20.013 --> 11:22.981
As applejack, I'll never get him
interested in the festival.

11:22.983 --> 11:24.282
The festival.

11:24.284 --> 11:28.920
And I do appreciate
your help ever so much.

11:28.922 --> 11:32.257
I couldn't do a thing
without you spikey poo.

11:32.259 --> 11:35.026
Well... That's what
friends are for.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.728
Right! So!

11:36.730 --> 11:41.933
Come... On... Farm thing!

11:41.935 --> 11:43.201
<i>(sigh)</i>

11:44.438 --> 11:49.908
<i>Applejack: Well, it would help</i>
<i>if the harness was on right.</i>

11:49.910 --> 11:51.843
What are you doing?

11:51.845 --> 11:54.245
I'm simply lending a
hoof with the chores...

11:54.247 --> 11:56.715
...Which I love
doing ever so much.

11:58.384 --> 12:01.119
Well, if you're still
interested after the festival,

12:01.121 --> 12:03.188
I can teach you all about it.

12:03.190 --> 12:06.458
But right now, I need to get the
plowing done if you don't mind.

12:08.728 --> 12:09.894
Not at all.

12:10.930 --> 12:12.330
(grunt)

12:12.332 --> 12:14.232
She makes it look so easy.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.900
I know.

12:15.902 --> 12:17.969
Isn't she fantastic?

12:21.373 --> 12:22.841
<i>(crash)</i>

12:27.146 --> 12:29.748
I really don't see what
the fuss is all about.

12:32.818 --> 12:34.919
Now, rarity, you be careful.

12:34.921 --> 12:37.122
If you don't get the
bucking just right,

12:37.124 --> 12:39.023
<i>You could sprain a hoof.</i>

12:39.025 --> 12:41.493
I am perfectly familiar with
the applebucking process,

12:41.495 --> 12:45.797
Thank you very much, but while
you seem to rely on raw power,

12:45.799 --> 12:49.067
I believe a certain amount
of style is required.

12:49.069 --> 12:51.870
It's really more of a
dance, if you ask me.

12:51.872 --> 12:55.974
♪

12:59.879 --> 13:01.913
Et voilà.

13:01.915 --> 13:05.116
Well, your way is
definitely long on style.

13:05.118 --> 13:10.822
Now if you'll all excuse me,
I have some more chores to do.

13:10.824 --> 13:12.357
Inside!

13:15.194 --> 13:16.394
<i>(slam)</i>

13:17.363 --> 13:20.165
Rarity, can I ask
you something?

13:20.167 --> 13:23.501
Why, trend, you can
ask me anything.

13:23.503 --> 13:27.438
I've been meaning to ask
for a while and, frankly,

13:27.440 --> 13:29.474
I'm sort of embarrassed.

13:30.442 --> 13:32.343
Rarity...

13:32.345 --> 13:37.482
Do you think applejack would
be my date for the festival?

13:37.484 --> 13:39.884
Why don't you go ask
her yourself?

13:54.433 --> 13:55.500
<i>(slam)</i>

13:55.502 --> 13:56.501
Phew!

13:56.503 --> 14:01.272
If you've come to apologize,
there's really no need.

14:01.274 --> 14:03.174
What are you talking about?

14:03.176 --> 14:05.910
Let's dispense with
the charade, shall we?

14:05.912 --> 14:08.613
Listen, I know you really
want trend to like you.

14:08.615 --> 14:10.081
And he does.

14:10.083 --> 14:13.017
Despite somepony's
best efforts.

14:13.019 --> 14:16.421
I swear, I don't know why he's
paying so much attention to me.

14:16.423 --> 14:19.591
And I don't know anypony who's
that interested in farming.

14:19.593 --> 14:24.495
Well, maybe it's time trend
met a  <u>real</u> country pony.

14:24.497 --> 14:28.967
<i>Instead of coming up with</i>
<i>new ways to impress trend?</i>

14:28.969 --> 14:31.002
Oh, I'm sure you'd love that.

14:31.004 --> 14:33.504
Well, I have a new
vision for the festival.

14:33.506 --> 14:36.341
(puts on country accent)
and it's gonna be more country

14:36.343 --> 14:39.544
Than the whole apple
family put together!

14:43.482 --> 14:47.919
Um, isn't it a little late
to be changing the theme?

14:47.921 --> 14:50.355
Applejack, what's going on?

14:50.357 --> 14:52.190
I'm too scared to guess.

14:52.192 --> 14:57.161
<i>Rarity: Firstly, I just wanna</i>
<i>thank you'all for comin'</i>

14:57.163 --> 14:59.898
<i>And second I know</i>
<i>y'all will all adore</i>

14:59.900 --> 15:02.200
<i>My new festival theme...</i>

15:02.202 --> 15:07.906
<i>♪ (banjo)</i>

15:07.908 --> 15:10.174
Simple ways!

15:18.550 --> 15:21.552
<i>(laughter)</i>

15:21.554 --> 15:24.155
Well, what's so funny?

15:24.157 --> 15:28.192
Rarity, that is the silliest
getup I have ever seen.

15:28.194 --> 15:30.094
It is a little funny.

15:30.096 --> 15:31.296
Funny?

15:31.298 --> 15:35.366
Rarity, you aren't
serious, are you?

15:35.368 --> 15:37.001
Well, of course I'm serious!

15:37.003 --> 15:38.169
Ahem...

15:38.171 --> 15:40.204
Why wouldn't I be?

15:40.206 --> 15:42.640
Because you would
never dress like that.

15:42.642 --> 15:46.210
You like fashion and high
society and fancy things.

15:46.212 --> 15:50.648
And I can like plowing fields
and hauling apples just as much.

15:50.650 --> 15:53.952
How do you know
what I like?

15:53.954 --> 15:55.720
Because I know you.

15:55.722 --> 15:59.691
Well, maybe you don't know
me as well as you think.

15:59.693 --> 16:02.994
And I suppose it's just a
coincidence that trenderhoof

16:02.996 --> 16:05.463
Seems so interested
in country life too?

16:05.465 --> 16:07.999
I don't know what
you're gettin' at.

16:08.001 --> 16:10.401
Well, then I guess I'll
just have to show you.

16:10.403 --> 16:15.173
Now, if y'all will excuse
me, I have a hootenanny

16:15.175 --> 16:17.275
Of a festival to put on.

16:17.277 --> 16:19.010
<i>(door closes)</i>

16:19.012 --> 16:20.578
<i>(growl)</i>

16:24.283 --> 16:28.453
Now, to be a model in the
simple ways fashion show,

16:28.455 --> 16:32.023
You might think simple
means less is more.

16:32.025 --> 16:34.559
Well, that just ain't so.

16:34.561 --> 16:38.329
If you want to be real
simple, more is more.

16:45.337 --> 16:49.307
Now y'all go off and make
yourselves look just like that.

16:53.645 --> 16:59.017
Who's our next model
for the fashion show?

16:59.019 --> 17:00.184
Um...

17:00.186 --> 17:02.453
Apple jewel?

17:02.455 --> 17:04.155
Who the hay is that?

17:04.157 --> 17:14.232
♪

17:14.234 --> 17:24.242
♪

17:24.244 --> 17:26.377
Is this some kinda joke?

17:26.379 --> 17:31.649
Why, rarity, what ever would
make you think I was joking?

17:31.651 --> 17:34.485
Because you would never
wear an ensemble like that!

17:34.487 --> 17:37.288
You like plowing fields
and hauling apples...

17:37.290 --> 17:40.792
And I can like
fashion just as much.

17:40.794 --> 17:46.197
Well, maybe you do not know
me as well as you think.

17:46.199 --> 17:49.834
But I got a whole
festival to plan,

17:49.836 --> 17:53.438
So if you're gonna start
modelin', just get on with it.

17:56.341 --> 17:59.177
Life is a festival, and you
should celebrate it

17:59.179 --> 18:04.282
By looking just like me, because
I'm a trend-setting fashionista!

18:07.219 --> 18:10.388
You're a trend-setting
fashionista?

18:10.390 --> 18:12.790
Why that's the most ridiculous
thing I've ever--

18:12.792 --> 18:15.760
I mean, good for you.

18:15.762 --> 18:19.597
I, on the other hoof, couldn't
care less how I look

18:19.599 --> 18:22.300
Long as I get the chores done.

18:24.770 --> 18:27.405
Oh? Is that so?

18:27.407 --> 18:29.740
Yes indeedy doodle.

18:29.742 --> 18:31.676
Not me.

18:31.678 --> 18:35.480
My mane needs to be perfectly
coiffed at all times.

18:35.482 --> 18:40.685
Well, my mane is full
of dust and split ends.

18:40.687 --> 18:44.856
My hooves are so polished you
can see your reflection in them.

18:44.858 --> 18:49.427
My hooves are cracked and dry
from working in the fields!

18:49.429 --> 18:51.863
I'm so fashion forward.

18:51.865 --> 18:54.298
I wear droopy drawers.

18:54.300 --> 18:56.667
I smell like rosebuds.

18:56.669 --> 18:59.303
I love being covered in mud!

19:00.539 --> 19:01.772
<i>(splat)</i>

19:05.210 --> 19:06.477
<i>(splash)</i>

19:08.881 --> 19:11.482
Goodness! Your couture!

19:11.484 --> 19:13.184
Oh, it's bad.

19:14.286 --> 19:16.354
Will somepony
bring me a towel

19:16.356 --> 19:19.257
To wipe this repulsive
filth from my hooves!

19:19.259 --> 19:21.359
There's the rarity I know!

19:21.361 --> 19:25.263
Oh, applejack, I'm sorry
I said all those things.

19:25.265 --> 19:27.265
You're a true friend who
probably knows me better

19:27.267 --> 19:32.570
I don't know what I was thinking
wearing this ridiculous outfit.

19:32.572 --> 19:34.639
I kinda know how you feel.

19:34.641 --> 19:37.708
But you were just trying to help
me see how silly I was being.

19:37.710 --> 19:39.544
And you were right.

19:39.546 --> 19:43.247
Besides, that gown
looks just gorgeous on you.

19:43.249 --> 19:45.416
I wish I hadn't ruined it.

19:45.418 --> 19:47.418
Thanks. It's
nice ain't it?

19:47.420 --> 19:48.819
It's magnificent!

19:48.821 --> 19:50.655
Wherever did
you get it?

19:50.657 --> 19:53.324
Oh. It's uh... One of yours.

19:56.195 --> 19:58.696
I'll need 3 gallons of boiling
water and one ounce of detergent

19:58.698 --> 19:59.864
Stat!

20:00.766 --> 20:02.466
<i>(ahem)</i>

20:02.468 --> 20:05.736
I'm moving to ponyville!

20:05.738 --> 20:09.607
Being the most interesting pony
in equestria is exhausting.

20:09.609 --> 20:12.343
I want to leave my exotic,
exciting life behind

20:12.345 --> 20:14.545
And live on a farm.

20:14.547 --> 20:18.916
Well, that's real nice, but I
sure hope you weren't thinking

20:18.918 --> 20:20.851
Of sweet apple acres.

20:20.853 --> 20:23.421
Oh.

20:23.423 --> 20:27.792
Look, you're a fine
pony, but uh, well, I'm...

20:27.794 --> 20:30.528
I think what applejack
is trying to say,

20:30.530 --> 20:32.897
Is that there's something
unappealing about a pony

20:32.899 --> 20:36.500
Who'd change themselves so much
just to impress somepony else.

20:36.502 --> 20:40.638
If somepony doesn't like you for
who you are, it's their loss.

20:41.974 --> 20:44.275
Well, this is awkward.

20:44.277 --> 20:45.343
Not at all.

20:45.345 --> 20:48.980
I think I know
just how you feel.

20:48.982 --> 20:53.517
Is it too late to go
back to small town chic?

20:53.519 --> 20:54.919
Not if I can help it!

20:58.390 --> 21:00.658
<i>Rarity: Organizing the</i>
<i>ponyville days celebration</i>

21:00.660 --> 21:02.860
<i>Was one of the hardest</i>
<i>things I've ever done...</i>

21:02.862 --> 21:06.264
<i>♪ (orchestral waltz)</i>

21:06.266 --> 21:09.500
<i>But I learned an</i>
<i>important lesson.</i>

21:09.502 --> 21:13.271
<i>Real friends will like</i>
<i>you for who you are</i>

21:13.273 --> 21:17.275
And changing yourself to impress
them is no way to make new ones.

21:17.277 --> 21:20.411
<i>♪ (classical waltz)</i>

21:20.413 --> 21:22.680
<i>And when you're as</i>
<i>fabulous as I am...</i>

21:22.682 --> 21:27.585
♪

21:27.587 --> 21:29.420
<i>It's practically a crime.</i>

21:29.422 --> 21:31.555
♪ (waltz ends)
